<article>
    <h1>CIN&#xAD;DERELLA TREAT&#xAD;MENT AT WALK&#xAD;ING ON SUN&#xAD;SHINE</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201225/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-25"><time>2020-12-25</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE STYLE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Best for tired tresses, overly frizzy or dam­aged hair, the Korean Cin­derella Treat­ment will take you from pump­kin to princess in an hour.</p>
    <p>Of­fered at pop­u­lar cafe-sa­lon Walk­ing On Sun­shine, the form of ker­atin treat­ment uses or­ganic Korean brand Na­turia to tame frizzi­ness. The eco-friendly for­mula is packed with or­ganic in­gre­di­ents such as aloe vera and col­la­gen, min­imis­ing the use of harsh chem­i­cals.</p>
    <p>Un­like reg­u­lar hair treat­ments, the Cin­derella Treat­ment re­quires the use of a hair iron to “seal” the prod­uct into the hair. It has a slight re­bond­ing or straight­en­ing ef­fect and leaves the hair smooth, silky and glossy for up to two months.</p>
    <p>The sa­lon alone – opened in 2018 by beauty and life­style group</p>
    <p>Ini­tia, which also owns Korean beauty sa­lon Leekaja here – is worth a visit for its ex­u­ber­ant vibes.</p>
    <p>Cub­bies teem with plants and ev­ery nook is niftily out­fit­ted with Dyson hair tools and Bose speak­ers pip­ing pop hits. It has been dubbed a mil­len­nial favourite for its In­sta­gram po­ten­tial, but is pop­u­lar with peo­ple of all ages.</p>
    <p>Get an all-in-one pam­per­ing fix there too – ba­sic man­i­cures or fin­ger mask and hand mas­sage are free while you have your hair dressed, sub­ject to man­i­curists’ avail­abil­ity.</p>
    <p>The sa­lon also of­fers a full menu of nail- and foot-care ser­vices, in­clud­ing for kids ($15 a man­i­cure).</p>
    <p>Cus­tomers can or­der food and drinks from the sa­lon’s ad­join­ing cafe.</p>
    <p>Start­ing at $300 for short hair, the Cin­derella Treat­ment is a splurge (a bot­tle of Na­turia sham­poo costs $85.60) but could be the trick to start­ing the new year fresh.</p>
    <p>Info: 03-07 Or­chard Cen­tral,</p>
    <p>181 Or­chard Road. For book­ings, call 8877-8800 or go to walkingon­sun­shine.sg</p>

